stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> Computed
  Computed --> PlanCaptured: lifecycle plan recorded
  PlanCaptured --> WrittenUnverified: governed write applied
  WrittenUnverified --> Accepted: required validation, reproducibility and gates pass

  Computed --> Abandoned: render or contract validation fails
  PlanCaptured --> Abandoned: stale, unauthorized, cancelled or superseded
  WrittenUnverified --> Abandoned: post-write validation or gate fails

  Abandoned --> Computed: new refresh attempt
  Accepted --> Computed: new refresh attempt after source, target, base or contract change

  note right of Accepted
    Acceptance applies to its recorded scope.
    Drift starts a new attempt and does not silently
    rewrite the prior recorded trust state.
    DPA-500 may explicitly invalidate a scope through
    a governed finding or gate rule.
  end note

  note right of PlanCaptured
    This is a consumer trust state.
    The document-status token planned is not used here.
  end note

  note right of Abandoned
    Non-accepted attempt only.
    Its bytes must never be presented as accepted.
  end note
